title: Two Error: FileNotFoundError: No unfiltered data file found,  ValueError: Unrecognized track_method=
body: ### Is there an existing issue for this? - [X] I have searched the existing issues ### Bug description Hi DLC team, I encountered the same error as #1626 . However, it behaves a little differently. If you analyze_video to the original video used for learning, .csv, .h5, .pickle files will be output. However, when I try to apply to other videos, only .csv files are output and there are no .h5, .pickle files. I get FileNotFoundError: No unfiltered data file found and ValueError: Unrecognized track_method= Also, strangely, you can apply to videos shot with iphone, but you cannot apply to videos shot with GoProb on same config.yaml. Only csv files will appear. Is it still an encoding problem like #1626 If so, can you tell me a good way to re-encode? Thank you ### Operating System Windows10 ### DeepLabCut version deeplabcut==2.2.1 ### DeepLabCut mode single animal ### Device type GPU - NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3080 ### Steps To Reproduce 1. labeling, traning and evaluate network is OK 2. analyze video - save csv -> yes - save nwb -> yes - filter prediction -> no - dynamically crop bodyparts -> no - plots to pop up -> no - plot trajectory -> yes ### Relevant log output ```shell Starting GUI...
